Description: Crib Social offers a platform to meet new people and make new friends.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: CribSocial provides a platform for social interaction between people through activities of similar interests.  The service allows people to create and participate in activities and events in their local area. One can create and participate in any type of social activity ranging in categories from food, dance, education, movies etc. People can look for a dance partner or someone to go to the movies with, or just someone to play tennis with. The service also allows users to create and organize social groups that meet regularly as well as publish one time events such as a concert or a sport event and invite people to join. Cribsocial's mission is to get people to socialize with real people with similar interests. It is not a social networking website, but rather a way for people to get off the computer and get out and experience the world. CribSocial's service is completely free and straightforward. People can search for activities and events in their local area using keywords, category, participants, and proximity by zip code. The location of activities is also shown in a map for a better geographical understanding of the location.  In order to create or participate in activities the service requires to create an account. Creating an activity is relatively straightforward and requires simple information such as category,location, date-time and activity description. Once the activity is created it is instantly available to the world to participate.

Description: ChargeBackChampion provides Consumer Verification Alerts to any business that is accepting debit & credit cards online.
Full Description: ChargeBackChampion provides Consumer Verification Alerts to any business that is accepting debit & credit cards online. Online businesses must be able to accept debit & credit cards in order to produce cashflow. However, online businesses generally have higher chargeback activity than a "Swiped" or "Brick & Mortar" merchant as purchases may not be recognized on a statement or now the growing trend is the increase in fraudulent or stolen credit card chargebacks. When an online merchant exceeds 1% in their chargeback ratio they become a problem account for the payment processor & subject to possible closure. When an online merchant exceeds 2%, they become classified as an excessive chargeback account by Visa/MC and force the payment processor to close the account. Consumer Verification Alerts allow the merchant to have advance notice of a chargeback and can resolve it before it becomes an actual chargeback thus keeping the ratio below Visa/MC thresholds.

Description: Simply manage your referral partner relationships. Easiest PRM software.
Full Description: PRMDeals grew out of a deep frustration with the “nickel and diming” of the Partner Relationship Management or Channel Relationship Management industry. Look around, search Google. You won’t find straight forward pricing information, a free trial or even helpful staff to answer a few basic questions.  The second reason and most important one at that is that they have been right where you are. Having successfully created several software platforms and technology products, they have been looking at ways to increase their efficiency, improve their sales and bring order into their new business development efforts. They had a ton of requests from vendors who wanted to market their product or at least refer us to their customers and earn commission for their efforts. Pretty simple stuff, but they simply did not have the tools to accommodate this. Download their free brochure. So they went out researched, called companies and sat through demos (heck they even had to pay for a few third rate system -- just to talk to sales). After analyzing what they had encountered, they realized that the PRM programs that were being offered lacked simplicity, were overpriced and terribly executed their basic requirements. They decided it was time to see if they could design a PRM system that they will be proud to use internally. They liked what they saw and decided to offer it to the world.

Industries: Apps, Audio, Developer APIs, Internet, Search Engine, Software
Description: Zypr aggregates proprietary 3rd-party APIs, categorizes their functions and then presents those functions through a single, normalized API.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: One account. Many services. Many devices. Zypr aggregates proprietary 3rd-party APIs, categorizes their functions and then presents those functions through a single, normalized API with full voice control on a wide range of platforms, including mobile, desktop, consumer electronics devices and auto infotainment.  By aggregating and normalizing 3rd party APIs, Zypr creates a stable access point for devices and apps to access those services without concern for service and API changes. Zypr’s voice client adapter entity provides voice control over all services regardless of provider or category. As such, Zypr enables a powerful natural language voice control metaphor for accessing a wide variety of service types. For example, instead of speaking to a single POI vendor like Yelp, a client can speak to the Zypr POI client adapter entity and have a single point of access to all the POI services integrated through Zypr. As services change or get swapped out, the client can continue to use POI services without any code changes. Also, by creating a single sign-on for the user, Zypr enables a unified service profile for the user across multiple devices. In addition, by creating a meta-level of access by service category, Zypr creates a unique ability for compelling mash-ups across services. For example, instead of mashing up “Twitter” with “Tuner2”, a Zypr client can integrate Social Networking and Internet Radio generically such that no matter what services are selected by the end user, the two services are integrated through Zypr. This effect is both a benefit to the end user and a dramatic simplification for the developer.
Industry Groups: Apps, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Software

Full Description: Parallella is a credit card-sized computer based on the Epiphany multi-core chips from [Adapteva](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/adapteva), that aims to democratize access to parallel computing. It can be used as a standalone computer, an embedded device or as a component in a scaled out parallel server cluster. Parallella includes a low power dual core ARM A9 processor and runs several of the popular Linux distributions, including Ubuntu. The Epiphany co-processor chips consists of an array of RISC processors programmable in bare metal C/C++ or in a parallel programming frameworks such as OpenCL, MPI, and OpenMP. It is applied in solutions developed for various sectors: consumer, computing infrastructure, military and aerospace, medical, communication, and industrial and instrumentation.
